    triggerDescription: 'user is thinking about buying a home or wants to know if they are ready to become a homeowner',
    instructions: 'Home buying readiness has clear financial prerequisites that many agents will not tell buyers.\n1. Ask their target home price and location — this sets the scale of everything else\n2. Calculate the required down payment: 20% to avoid PMI, or ask if they are considering lower down payment options and what those cost monthly\n3. Check cash reserves beyond the down payment: closing costs (2-5% of purchase price), moving costs, and 3-6 months of mortgage payment reserves\n4. Calculate their debt-to-income ratio: total monthly debt payments divided by gross monthly income — lenders typically require under 43%\n5. Ask their current credit score — below 620 is a barrier for conventional loans; 740+ gets the best rates\n6. Estimate the true monthly cost of ownership: mortgage principal + interest, property tax, insurance, HOA if any, maintenance budget (1% of home value annually)\n7. Compare rent vs. buy: at current rates, buying often costs significantly more monthly than renting an equivalent space — be honest about the math\n8. Give a clear readiness verdict: ready now, ready in X months with these specific actions, or not ready and here is why\nOwning a home is a lifestyle decision as much as a financial one. Present the full cost before they fall in love with a listing.',
    outputFormat: 'Target price → down payment needed → cash reserves check → debt-to-income ratio → credit score assessment → true monthly ownership cost → rent vs buy comparison → readiness verdict',
