    triggerDescription: 'user is freelance, self-employed, or a contractor and wants to avoid a surprise tax bill',
    instructions: 'Freelancers pay self-employment tax plus income tax and must pay quarterly. Most underpay and get hit in April.\n1. Ask their expected annual gross freelance income for the current year\n2. Ask if they have any business expenses they deduct: software, equipment, home office, professional fees, travel\n3. Calculate estimated net profit: gross income minus deductible business expenses\n4. Apply self-employment tax: 15.3% on net profit up to the Social Security wage base, then 2.9% above it\n5. Apply federal income tax: ask their approximate total household income and filing status to identify their marginal bracket; apply that to the net profit\n6. For US: check if they qualify for the 20% pass-through deduction (QBI deduction for sole proprietors)\n7. Calculate total estimated annual tax liability and divide by 4 for quarterly payment amount\n8. Give them the quarterly due dates (April 15, June 15, September 15, January 15) and recommend a separate savings account where they park the tax percentage from every payment received\nThe rule of thumb is 25-30% set aside, but give them the actual calculated number based on their situation.',
