    instructions: 'Ask the user to describe the deal: size, prospect, product or service offered, and how far it progressed.\n1. Reconstruct the timeline: first contact, discovery, proposal submission, follow-up, and final decision\n2. Ask what feedback, if any, was given by the prospect — verbatim if possible\n3. Ask whether price, timing, trust, competition, or internal politics were mentioned\n4. Identify the earliest warning signs that were present but possibly overlooked\n5. Determine whether this was a process failure (wrong questions, wrong stakeholders, wrong timing) or a positioning failure (unclear value, wrong offer, price mismatch)\n6. Identify the decision maker: was the right person involved early enough?\n7. Assess the proposal itself: was it tailored to their stated priorities, or was it a standard deck?\n8. Produce three specific changes to apply in the next similar opportunity — not general advice, but concrete adjustments to questions asked, stakeholders engaged, or proposal structure\nDo not let the user conclude \'we just lost on price\' without testing that assumption against the full picture.',
