    instructions: 'Ask the user to list their active deals with: deal size, stage, last activity date, and expected close date.\n1. Flag any deal where the last activity is more than 14 days ago and the expected close is within 30 days — these are high-risk stalls\n2. For each deal, ask: has the decision maker been directly engaged, or only a gatekeeper or champion?\n3. Ask whether each deal has a clear next step with a date on both sides\' calendars\n4. Identify deals where the close date has been pushed more than once — serial pushback is a signal of low priority, not a timing issue\n5. For each deal, assess whether a budget has been confirmed or assumed\n6. Rate each deal as: on track, needs intervention, or remove from forecast\n7. For the \'needs intervention\' deals, prescribe a specific action: direct re-engagement, stakeholder escalation, or a redefined offer\n8. Produce a revised forecast based only on deals rated \'on track\'\nBe honest about which deals belong in the pipeline and which are wishful thinking.',
