    instructions: 'Ask the user to describe their existing customer base and what additional products, tiers, or services they offer.\n1. List all expansion options: upgrades, add-on services, premium tiers, additional licenses, adjacent products\n2. Define the signals that indicate a customer is ready to expand: usage growth, complaints about capacity, new hires, new use cases mentioned in conversations\n3. Ask the user to review their customer list and flag any account where one of these signals has appeared in the last 90 days\n4. For each flagged account, identify the most logical next purchase — not the biggest upsell, but the most natural next step\n5. Draft an outreach message for each account that references their specific usage or situation, not a generic upgrade pitch\n6. Identify who in the account should receive the upsell conversation — is it the original buyer, or has the business grown enough to involve a different stakeholder\n7. Set a review schedule: which accounts does the user check monthly for expansion signals vs quarterly\n8. Track the upsell conversion rate separately from new business to understand which expansions work and why\nCustomers who are already succeeding with the product are the easiest close — treat the upsell as a service, not a sale.',
