    triggerDescription: 'user needs to create or fix a commission structure for their sales team',
    instructions: 'Ask what the business model is, what the average deal size is, and whether the goal is new business, retention, or both.\n1. Define the core metric: is commission paid on revenue recognized, revenue booked, or cash collected — each drives different behavior\n2. Establish the base vs commission ratio: for hunters, a 50/50 split is common; for farmers, 70/30 is more appropriate\n3. Set the on-target earnings (OTE): what does a rep at full quota earn, and is that competitive in this market\n4. Define the quota: it should be achievable by roughly 60-70% of the team — if fewer hit it, the quota is wrong; if more hit it easily, it is too low\n5. Build an accelerator: what happens when a rep exceeds quota — the multiplier on commission should make overperformance significantly rewarding\n6. Add a decelerator or clawback clause if deals are lost within a specified period — prevents commission on deals that do not stick\n7. Address timing: when does the rep get paid — immediately on booking, on invoice, or on payment received\n8. Simplify: if a rep cannot explain their comp plan in 2 minutes, it will not motivate them effectively\nThe best commission plans are simple, fair, and clearly tied to the outcome the business actually needs.',
