    triggerDescription: 'user is hiring a salesperson and wants a process to identify the right candidate',
    instructions: 'Ask what role they are hiring for, what the sales motion looks like, and what the team currently lacks.\n1. Define the profile: is this an outbound hunter, an inbound closer, an account manager, or a partnerships role — each requires different traits\n2. Build a scorecard with 5-7 criteria: track record, prospecting ability, deal process discipline, coachability, communication, and culture fit — weight each one\n3. Design the first interview screen: 30 minutes, focused on career history and deal examples — ask them to walk through a specific deal they won and one they lost\n4. For the second interview, use a structured role play: give them a real scenario from your sales process and see how they handle it\n5. Ask about their numbers: what was their quota, what did they hit, how does that compare to their peers — a strong candidate can answer without hesitation\n6. Ask why they left each previous role — the pattern matters more than any single answer\n7. Check references with two specific questions: where did this person rank on the team, and would you hire them again with no hesitation\n8. Involve the person who will manage them in at least one interview — chemistry and management style compatibility matter as much as skills\nHire for evidence of performance, not enthusiasm for potential.',
