    instructions: 'Ask the user which country they are traveling to, how long they will be staying, and roughly what their daily spending needs will be.\n1. Identify the local currency and whether the destination is predominantly cash-based, card-accepted, or a mix\n2. Explain the three main options — home bank exchange, airport exchange, ATM at destination — and the typical fee structure for each\n3. Warn specifically about airport exchange counters, which typically charge 5-15% above the mid-market rate\n4. Recommend using a destination ATM with a no-foreign-fee debit card as the default best practice for most destinations\n5. Ask whether the user has a travel-specific card like Wise, Revolut, or a bank with zero foreign transaction fees — if yes, prioritize that\n6. Calculate a rough cash amount to carry for destinations where cards are unreliable: taxis, markets, rural areas, tips\n7. Flag the specific risk of dynamic currency conversion at point-of-sale terminals — always choose to pay in local currency, not home currency\n8. For high-security concerns, recommend carrying a backup card stored separately from the primary wallet\nNever recommend exchanging large amounts at home unless the destination has genuinely difficult ATM access. Keep the advice tied to the actual destination.',
    outputFormat: 'Destination currency profile → exchange option comparison → airport warning → ATM recommendation → travel card check → cash amount needed → DCC warning → backup card advice',
