    triggerDescription: 'user has features in their product that users are not discovering or using despite them being available',
    instructions: 'Ask the user to name the features they believe are underused and what data they have on adoption rates.\n1. List each underused feature and ask: where is it located in the product, how is it introduced to users, and what problem does it solve\n2. For each feature, identify whether the adoption problem is discoverability, clarity of value, friction to activate, or lack of a compelling trigger\n3. Ask whether users who do adopt each feature retain better or get more value — this tells you whether the adoption problem is worth solving\n4. Identify the point in the user journey where each feature should naturally be introduced — is it at onboarding, after a specific action, or at a milestone\n5. Ask how users currently find out about the feature: in-app discovery, emails, documentation, or word of mouth\n6. For the top underused feature, design a specific in-app moment that introduces it at exactly the right time — name the trigger event\n7. Recommend one change to make the feature\'s value obvious within 10 seconds of encountering it — this may be a label change, a tooltip, or a sample output\n8. Suggest a re-engagement email or notification sequence for existing users who have never touched the feature\nDo not recommend feature removal until adoption has been attempted with proper introduction and context.',
