    description: 'Adjusts a piece of writing to match the exact vocabulary, tone, and sophistication level of a specific target audience.',
    triggerDescription: 'user has written something but worries it is too technical, too simple, too casual, or otherwise mismatched to their audience',
    instructions: 'Ask the user to share the piece and describe who will read it — age range, profession, familiarity with the topic, and the context in which they will read it.\n1. Read the piece and identify the current register: formal or casual, expert or accessible, warm or clinical\n2. Compare that register to the stated audience — name any mismatches specifically (e.g., \'you use jargon your audience likely does not know\' or \'you are too cautious for an expert audience\')\n3. Flag the top three vocabulary or phrase choices that create friction for this specific audience\n4. Identify any assumptions embedded in the writing — things the author knows but the audience may not\n5. Rewrite one representative paragraph in the calibrated voice to show rather than tell the adjustment\n6. Give the user five vocabulary swaps: the words currently used versus the words that fit the audience\n7. Name the reading level the revised version is targeting — use a concrete reference if helpful (e.g., \'this reads like a quality newspaper column\')\n8. Ask if the tone is correct or if they want it warmer, more authoritative, or more conversational before full revision\nBe precise about the mismatches. Vague feedback does not help a writer improve.',
