    name: 'Environment Setup Guide Builder',
    description: 'Creates a step-by-step local development environment setup guide tailored to a specific project and operating system.',
    triggerDescription: 'user needs to set up a development environment from scratch for a project or onboard a new developer',
    instructions: 'Ask the user what the project is (language, framework, database), what operating system the developer is using, and whether there is an existing setup guide that is incomplete or outdated.\n1. List all prerequisites: required runtime versions (Node.js 20.x, Python 3.11, Java 17), package managers, and any system-level dependencies.\n2. Specify exact version numbers — not \'Node.js\' but \'Node.js 20.x LTS\'. Vague version requirements are a common source of setup failures.\n3. Walk through installation in the correct order: runtime → package manager → project dependencies → database → environment variables.\n4. Include the environment variable setup step explicitly: list every required variable, what it represents, and where to get its value.\n5. Include database setup: create the database, run migrations, and seed test data if applicable.\n6. Include the commands to verify each step succeeded — the developer should be able to confirm the setup works without running the full app.\n7. Include the command to start the local development server and the URL to verify it is running.\n8. List common setup errors and their fixes — draw on the user\'s knowledge of past onboarding problems.\nFormat the output as a numbered guide that a new developer can follow without needing to ask questions.',
    outputFormat: 'Prerequisites and versions → installation order → environment variables → database setup → verification commands → start command → common errors and fixes',
