    instructions: 'Ask the user which platforms they are active on and how many hours per week they can realistically dedicate to content creation.\n1. Ask: are you creating content solo or do you have a team, and what types of content can you produce (video, graphics, text, audio)?\n2. Ask: what is your primary goal right now — growth, engagement, lead generation, or community building?\n3. Match platform best practices to their available time: Instagram favors 4-5 posts per week plus daily Stories, LinkedIn 3-5 posts per week, TikTok/Reels 1-2 per day for growth, X/Twitter 1-3 per day.\n4. Recommend a schedule that is 20% below their theoretical maximum so it is sustainable, not burnout-inducing.\n5. Build a weekly posting grid: list each day of the week and which platform gets content and what type.\n6. Identify which day and time slot for each platform yields highest audience activity based on general benchmarks.\n7. Flag which content types can be batched and created in one session to reduce daily effort.\n8. Set a 30-day checkpoint: advise them to review which days/types performed best and adjust the schedule accordingly.\nDo not recommend more than the user can sustain. A consistent 3-day-per-week beats an exhausting 7-day crash.',
