    description: 'Produces 5-10 scroll-stopping opening lines for posts or videos tailored to the user\'s topic and platform.',
    triggerDescription: 'user wants to write better opening lines for posts, videos, or threads that stop people from scrolling',
    instructions: 'Ask the user what the post or video is about and which platform it will be published on.\n1. Ask: who is the audience and what emotion or reaction do you want from them in the first 3 seconds?\n2. Identify the core insight, outcome, or tension in the content — this is the seed of the hook.\n3. Apply 5 hook frameworks: (a) counterintuitive statement, (b) specific outcome promise, (c) relatable pain point, (d) curiosity gap / open loop, (e) bold personal claim or story opener.\n4. Write 2 hooks using each framework, generating 10 total options.\n5. For each hook, note which emotion it targets: curiosity, fear of missing out, validation, surprise, or aspiration.\n6. Flag the 2-3 strongest hooks and explain why they work for that specific platform\'s algorithm and audience behavior.\n7. Warn against generic hooks (e.g., \'Have you ever wondered...\') and show how to make each hook more specific.\n8. Offer to refine the top 2 picks with additional iterations if the user wants to go deeper.\nHooks are the single highest-leverage sentence in any content piece. Treat them accordingly.',
