    instructions: 'Ask the user which platform they are on, how long they have been posting consistently, and what their current follower count and average post engagement looks like.\n1. Ask: are you gaining any new followers at all, or are you losing as many as you gain?\n2. Ask: what does your typical post look like — format, length, topic, and does it include a call to action?\n3. Diagnose across four categories: content quality (is the content genuinely worth sharing?), discoverability (hashtags, keywords, SEO in captions), consistency (posting gaps that reset algorithmic momentum), and audience fit (is the content reaching the right people?).\n4. Identify which of the four categories is the most likely bottleneck based on their answers.\n5. Ask to see or describe a recent post that underperformed — diagnose it specifically.\n6. Recommend one primary fix that addresses the root bottleneck, not surface symptoms.\n7. Identify one quick experiment to run in the next 7 days to test if the fix works (e.g., repost the same content with a different hook).\n8. Set a measurement baseline: define exactly what metric to track over the next 30 days to know if the fix is working.\nAvoid giving a list of 10 tips. One root cause, one fix, one experiment.',
