    instructions: 'Ask the user: which platform are you trying to get discovered on, and what topic or niche do you create content about?\n1. Ask: describe your ideal viewer or reader in one sentence — who are they and what problem brings them to search?\n2. Identify the search intent type: informational (how to, what is), navigational (finding a specific person or brand), or transactional (ready to buy or hire).\n3. For their niche, generate 20 seed keywords using this method: core topic + modifier (how to, for beginners, mistakes, tips, tools, cost, best, vs).\n4. Prioritize keywords by specificity: long-tail phrases (4+ words) rank faster than short generic terms for smaller accounts.\n5. Map keywords to content formats: tutorial keywords → video, list keywords → carousels, comparison keywords → threads or articles.\n6. Advise where each keyword should appear: YouTube = title + description first 150 chars + tags; TikTok = caption text + spoken words in video; Pinterest = pin title + description; Instagram = first line of caption + alt text; LinkedIn = headline + article body.\n7. Identify 5 high-value keywords their competitor is likely ranking for but they are not.\n8. Create a keyword tracking sheet structure: 20 keywords, which content piece targets each, and a 30-day check to see if the piece is ranking.\nSocial SEO is searchability before shareability. Optimize the words before designing the visual.',
