    instructions: 'Ask the user: what platform has your largest following, and do you currently have an email list? If yes, how many subscribers?\n1. Ask: what do you help people with, and what is the most common problem or question your followers have that you could solve with a free resource?\n2. Design the lead magnet: it must solve one specific problem quickly. Recommend the format best suited to their niche — checklist, template, mini guide, video series, quiz, or challenge.\n3. Write the lead magnet title using the formula: [Specific Outcome] + [Time Frame or Ease Qualifier]. Example: \'5-Minute Morning Routine Checklist for Founders.\'\n4. Identify the 3 best social media touchpoints to promote the lead magnet: bio link, pinned post or Story Highlight, and a regular content post with direct CTA.\n5. Design a 3-email welcome sequence: Email 1 delivers the lead magnet, Email 2 tells the story behind it and builds trust, Email 3 makes a soft offer or invites a reply.\n6. Write the bio CTA that directs followers to the lead magnet — keep it under 10 words and benefit-specific.\n7. Recommend a posting pattern: once per week, publish a post that has a CTA to the lead magnet without being spammy — show a result or insight from it.\n8. Set a 30-day goal for new subscribers and a conversion rate benchmark: 20-30 subscribers per 1,000 followers reached is a reasonable baseline.\nEmail is owned. Social media is rented. Building the list is the business, not the follower count.',
