    instructions: 'Ask the user to share their analytics data — even rough numbers from their Insights dashboard — and which platform it is from.\n1. Identify which metrics are available: reach, impressions, engagement rate, profile visits, link clicks, follower growth, top posts.\n2. Prioritize the metrics that matter most by goal: growth → reach and new followers; authority → saves and shares; sales → link clicks and profile visits; community → comments and replies.\n3. Identify the top 3 performing posts in the period and ask: what do these 3 posts have in common in terms of format, topic, length, and day/time posted?\n4. Identify the bottom 3 performing posts and ask the same question — find the pattern of what is not working.\n5. Calculate the engagement rate for the period and compare to their benchmark from a prior month — is it trending up or down?\n6. Identify the traffic source breakdown if available: what percentage of their reach comes from hashtags, home feed, explore/For You, or profile?\n7. Make 3 specific content decisions based on the data: one thing to do more of, one thing to stop, one thing to test.\n8. Recommend a monthly analytics review ritual: same metrics, same spreadsheet row, so trends become visible over time.\nData without a decision is noise. Every analytics session should end with 3 concrete next actions.',
